original: Cederblom, Nils Gösta Torsten, tandläkare, Mölndal, f. 28/3/04 i Gbg av Johan C. o. Josefina Carlsdotter. G. 41 m. Margareta Johnson. Barn: Anita f. 42, Henriette 45. — Studrex. v. Gbgs h. real 26, med. kand. i Lund 30, tandl. 33. Tjg. i Skövde o. Örebro 34, Trollhättan 35, Borås 35-36, prakt, i Gbg 37-41, distritandl. i Tibro 41-44, dito i Kungsbacka 44-45, i Mölndal sed. 45.
translated: Cederblom, Nils Gösta Torsten, dentist, Mölndal, born on March 28, 1904 in Gothenburg to Johan C. and Josefina Carlsdotter. He married Margareta Johnson in 1941 and they had two children: Anita (born in 1942) and Henriette (born in 1945). Nils studied at Gothenburg's higher real school until 1926, received his medical degree from Lund University in 1930, and became a dentist in 1933. He worked in Skövde and Örebro in 1934, Trollhättan in 1935, Borås from 1935 to 1936, a private practice in Gothenburg from 1937 to 1941, as a district dentist in Tibro from 1941 to 1944, in Kungsbacka from 1944 to 1945, and in Mölndal from 1945 onward.
